knight fellowships school me knight fellowships school me what makes a good school veronica anderson 2010 knight fellow founder schoolme chicago illinois anderson explored ways to virtually connect families schools and local communities around their common goals for students growth and academic success the foundation of the model is harnessing parents own expertise and experiences and using that information to enlighten educators and engage communities about ways schools can work better for children ultimately the mission of school me a social business enterprise is to close the achievement gap through informing and engaging parents which anderson calls the most potent resource yet to be meaningfully mobilized in efforts to reform public education tapping into stanford experts veronica anderson's fellowship bio contact anderson at anderson school me com stanford university
